# React / Component Rules (auto-attaches on *.tsx)

- **Function components + hooks only.** No class components, no `React.FC` typing —
  type props explicitly: `const Panel = ({ id }: PanelProps) => { ... }`.
- **No business logic in components.** UI components render `appState` and dispatch
  actions. Element mutations belong in the **Action system** (`actions/`), not in handlers.
- **Never mutate `appState` or elements directly.** Go through the action/`setState` path so
  history (undo/redo) stays consistent.
- **i18n:** user-facing strings come from the translation layer (`t("...")`), never hardcoded.
- **A11y:** interactive elements need an accessible name (`aria-label` or visible label) and
  keyboard handling; we ship to assistive-tech users.
- **Styling:** follow the existing SCSS module pattern in the package; do not add new CSS-in-JS libs.
- **Performance:** memoize expensive render paths; canvas-adjacent components must avoid
  re-rendering on every pointer move — throttle and use refs where the existing code does.

When you finish a `.tsx` change, confirm it has a Vitest test and passes `yarn test:typecheck`.
